If you click on image in media libary, you get various fields you can use. 
Title
Alternative Text
Caption
Description

So fill in the caption info for example: 

And these can all be grabbed and displayed on the page. 

<p class="caption f5 o-50 pt3 mv0>
  <?php echo wp_get_attachment_caption(54); ?>
</p>

The tachyons there gives it 
size f5
opacity 50%
padding top 3px
margin vertical 0

To add a new font, go to the top of header.php where you put in the googlefonts and at the end type &family=Archivo 

So it would look like this: 

<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Archivo+Black&family=Cardo:ital@0;1&family=Tenor+Sans&family=Archivo&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

Used to look like this: 

<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Archivo+Black&family=Cardo:ital@0;1&family=Tenor+Sans&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">